      "rationale": "Construct stiffness (N/mm) and peak rod bending moment predicted by FEA ensemble compared against experimental measurements using error metrics including mean absolute percentage error (MAPE=4.2%) and 95% prediction interval coverage. All ensemble members within experimental variability band."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and peak bending moment are the primary quantities of interest for ASTM F1717 compliance assessment and are directly linked to the clinical question of mechanical stability under physiological loading. These QoIs are standard outputs for spinal fixation device evaluation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
